  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nI'm trying to setup a secure system, where the validator password is stored in a Aegis Secure Key, so if the system in disconnected from power, it will not start validating when being plugged back in (see https://technicallynottechnical.medium.com/guide-to-securing-an-ethereum-2-0-validator-wallet-from-getting-slashed-due-to-theft-ubuntu-linux-89ad9233a67e),\r\n\r\nThe idea is that `validator_definitions.yml`, containing the password, is a symbolic link to the actual file stored in the Aegis Secure Key. I can setup this, but upon running it looks like lighthouse replaces the file `validator_definitions.yml`, so the symbolic link is replaced by the actual file.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse v2.1.4-98f7404\r\nBLS library: blst-modern\r\nSHA256 hardware acceleration: false\r\nSpecs: mainnet (true), minimal (false), gnosis (true)\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\n `validator_definitions.yml` should not be constantly rewritten, or there should be a command-line option allowing to specify its location (different from `--datadir`).\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nIf you have a suggestion, I'd like to know!\r\n",
